---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout
	title="Gene Tutorials"
	description="Progressive tutorials that teach the Gene programming language through hands-on projects."
>
	<header class="page-header">
		<h1>Tutorials</h1>
		<p>
			Gene tutorials guide you through real-world projects step by step. Each module reinforces language
			fundamentals, introduces new runtime concepts, and highlights best practices for macros, async flows, and
			modular design.
		</p>
	</header>

	<section class="tutorial-list">
		<article class="tutorial-card">
			<h2>Foundations: From REPL to CLI tool</h2>
			<p>
				Explore the basics of the language, define functions, and build a command-line utility that parses input and
				produces structured output.
			</p>
			<span class="meta">Status: In progress &middot; Target audience: New to Gene</span>
		</article>

		<article class="tutorial-card">
			<h2>Macros in production</h2>
			<p>
				Learn how Gene&apos;s macro system lets you craft domain-specific abstractions without sacrificing
				performance or readability.
			</p>
			<span class="meta">Status: Drafting &middot; Target audience: Intermediate</span>
		</article>

		<article class="tutorial-card">
			<h2>Async, generators, and structured concurrency</h2>
			<p>
				Compose futures, coordinate parallel tasks with task_scope, and process lazy sequences with
				generators. Covers async/await, fn*, yield, and shared-nothing threads with channels.
			</p>
			<span class="meta">Status: Planned &middot; Target audience: Intermediate to advanced</span>
		</article>

		<article class="tutorial-card">
			<h2>Capability sandboxing and safe execution</h2>
			<p>
				Learn Gene's deny-by-default capability model: grant, scope, and revoke permissions for file
				I/O, threads, and tool calling. Build a sandboxed script runner for AI agents.
			</p>
			<span class="meta">Status: Planned &middot; Target audience: Intermediate to advanced</span>
		</article>
	</section>

	<section class="cta">
		<h2>Want to contribute a tutorial?</h2>
		<p>
			We welcome community-authored walkthroughs. Share your idea by opening a GitHub issue to
			coordinate.
		</p>
                <a class="button primary" href="https://github.com/gcao/genex/discussions" rel="noopener">Discuss a tutorial idea</a>
	</section>
</Layout>

<style>
	.page-header {
		display: grid;
		gap: 0.75rem;
		margin-bottom: 3rem;
	}

	.page-header h1 {
		margin: 0;
		font-size: clamp(2.1rem, 3vw, 2.7rem);
	}

	.page-header p {
		color: var(--color-muted);
		max-width: 44rem;
		margin: 0;
	}

	.tutorial-list {
		display: grid;
		gap: 1.5rem;
	}

	.tutorial-card {
		background: var(--color-surface);
		border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
		border-radius: 1.1rem;
		padding: 1.75rem;
		box-shadow: 0 18px 32px rgba(15, 23, 42, 0.12);
		display: grid;
		gap: 0.85rem;
	}

	.tutorial-card h2 {
		margin: 0;
		font-size: 1.55rem;
	}

	.tutorial-card p {
		margin: 0;
		color: var(--color-muted);
	}

	.meta {
		font-size: 0.85rem;
		color: var(--color-muted);
		text-transform: uppercase;
		letter-spacing: 0.1em;
	}

	.cta {
		margin-top: 4rem;
		display: grid;
		gap: 0.75rem;
		max-width: 36rem;
	}

	.cta p {
		margin: 0;
		color: var(--color-muted);
	}

	.button {
		border-radius: 999px;
		padding: 0.65rem 1.6rem;
		font-weight: 600;
		display: inline-flex;
		align-items: center;
		border: 1px solid transparent;
		background: var(--color-accent);
		color: white;
		box-shadow: 0 12px 24px rgba(37, 99, 235, 0.2);
	}
</style>
